(secondQuint)Phase II Study of Atezolizumab + Bevacizumab in Endometrial Cancer.

 This phase 2 study using atezolizumab and bevacizumab aims to study the objective tumor response in women with recurrent endometrial cancer.

 Drugs will be administered via IV every 21 days until disease progression, unacceptable toxicity, or loss of clinical benefit as determined by investigator.

 Subjects will receive routine cancer care as well as tests and procedures required for the purposes of this study.

 It is expected this combination will be produce an anti-cancer effect with manageable toxicities in this patient population.

